The Herald Rutendo Rori Mash East Correspondent Former Education Minister and Mashonaland East Governor Aeneas Chigwedere has succumbed to Covid-19. Foreign Affairs and International Trade Deputy Minister Cde David Musabayana confirmed the death but could not give further details. In a related development former Zanu PF Chitumgwiza legislator and businessman Cde Christopher Chigumba died on Thursday night at a local hospital where he had been admitted. His son Takudzwa confirmed the death, saying details about the burial arrangements were to be availed in due course.